Observability for AWS CloudWatch Service (Platform Governance)

Created by: <Your Name> | Status: Draft | Last Updated: 2025-01-24
Epic: CloudWatch Service Ownership - Onboarding

1. General

This document establishes the "Monitor the Monitor" framework. It defines how we observe the Amazon CloudWatch service itself as a platform to ensure our telemetry pipeline is cost-effective, high-performing, and compliant with organizational SLOs.

Primary Objective: Ensure the reliability of the monitoring stack and prevent "blind spots" caused by platform failures or quotas.

Secondary Objective: Cost Governance and Lifecycle Management of logs/metrics.

2. Observability Best Practices

Adopt "Monitor the Monitor" Logic: Do not assume CloudWatch is always available. Monitor the InsufficientData rate to detect telemetry gaps.

Enforce Structured Logging (EMF): Prefer Embedded Metric Format (EMF) for application KPIs. This ensures logs and metrics are correlated by default while reducing the cost of separate PutMetricData calls.

Scale via OAM (Observability Access Manager): Use a Central Monitoring Account to aggregate cross-account/cross-region metrics. This avoids "Console Hopping" during incidents.

Treat Alarms as Code: All Alarms must explicitly define treatMissingData (breaching/notBreaching) to avoid flapping or silent failures.

Active Experience via Synthetics: Use CloudWatch Synthetics (Canaries) to validate the "Outside-In" view. If the Canary fails but internal metrics are green, the issue is likely at the network/edge layer.

Proactive Retention Management: Every Log Group must have a non-infinite retention policy. Use S3 for long-term archival to reduce CloudWatch storage costs by ~90%.

3. Key Metrics (Platform Signals)
Metric	Description	Source
CallCount / ThrottledCount	API request volume vs. requests denied by AWS Service Quotas.	AWS/CloudWatch
IncomingBytes	Volume of log data ingested. Primary driver of platform cost.	AWS/Logs
InsufficientDataRate	% of alarms unable to evaluate due to missing telemetry.	Metric Math
CanarySuccessPercent	Success rate of end-to-end Synthetics checks.	AWS/Synthetics
MetricStreamDeliveryErrors	Failures in streaming data to New Relic or Kinesis.	AWS/CloudWatch
