7. Runbook (Simplified)

If ThrottledCount is High: Check CloudTrail for "Who" is calling the API. Likely a misconfigured Lambda or a high-frequency New Relic polling script.

If InsufficientData is High: Check IncomingBytes. If bytes are down, the Log Agent/Fluentbit is likely crashed on the source instances.

If EstimatedCharges Spikes: Run the "Log Killers" query in Insights. Identify the specific service and contact the owner to reduce log verbosity (e.g., change DEBUG to INFO).

